title: invalid syntax (unclosed brace) yields eventual ICE: unexpected ty: [type error]

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: E-needs-test
labels.description: Call for participation: writing correctness tests

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
The following ICE's on stable, beta and nightly:
```Rust
use std::marker::PhantomData;

enum Bug {
    V = [PhantomData; { [ () ].len() ].len() as isize,
    //                ^
    //                + ---- this brace is never closed!!!
}
```

(notice the `{` was NOT closed)

<details>
<summary>Backtrace:</summary>

```
error: incorrect close delimiter: `]`
 --> src/lib.rs:4:38
  |
4 |     V = [PhantomData; { [ () ].len() ].len() as isize,
  |         -             -              ^ incorrect close delimiter
  |         |             |
  |         |             un-closed delimiter
  |         close delimiter possibly meant for this
```
